mpound names based on the element <i>goz</i> (from <i>gaut</i>, an ethnic name meaning ‘Geat’ or ‘Goth’; see   Goss  ).","alternatively, perhaps a diminutive of the Old French personal name <i>Josse</i> (Old Breton <i>Judoc</i>); see   Joyce  ."]}]},{"name":"Thomas","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["New Testament name, borne by one of Christ's twelve apostles, referred to as ‘Thomas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Josselyn was born about 1249, in Sawbridgeworth, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, Thomas Joslyn, was 21 and his mother, Maud Hyde, was 11247. He married Alice Liston about 1272, in Sawbridgeworth, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. He died in 1284, in his hometown, at the age of 36."},"et":{"about 1249–1284":"umbes 1249–1284","1249–1284":"1249–1284","1253–1275":"1253–1275","–Female":"Surnud","1273–1284":"1273–1284","1275–1323":"1275–1323","1229–1277":"1229–1277","1228–1277":"1228–1277","about 1272":"umbes 1272","1275":"1275","1286":"1286","1253":"1253","1284":"1284","1273":"1273","13 December 1275":"13. detsember 1275","1280":"1280","1228":"1228","1249":"1249","1323":"1323","1277":"1277","about 1248":"umbes 1248","about 1249":"umbes 1249"," 1277":"1277","about 1273":"umbes 1273","1229":"1229","Sawbridgeworth, Hertfordshire, England":"Sawbridgeworth, Hertfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hyde Hall, Sawbridgeworth, Hertfordshire, England":"Sawbridgeworth, Hertfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Shellow Bowells, Essex, England":"Shellow Bowells, Essex, England","Great Hyde Hall, Sa